{"履修期": "秋学期前半", "主な教授言語": "英語", "授業目的": "This\ncourse explores ethical issues in business and the foundational principles that\nunderpin decision-making in those contexts. It addresses key topics such as\nethical concepts, personal integrity, individual conscience, and social\nresponsibility, examining their influence on decision-making processes across\nvarious business functions. The course also emphasizes the development of\ncritical thinking skills to navigate complex ethical dilemmas and foster\nresponsible leadership in a dynamic business environment.", "到達目標": "At\nthe successful completion of this course, students will be able to:1.\nexhibit an understanding of ethical reasoning and ethical theory2.\nrecognize ethical issues in business related to integrity, objectivity, and\nindependence3.\napply ethical rules to specific business scenarios4.\nanalyze the key elements of an ethical controversy in business in relation to\nmoral philosophy, the influence of work groups,&nbsp; corporate culture, and\nsocial responsibility\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n5.\nevaluate the impact of ethical decision-making on stakeholders and\norganizational outcomes", "特記事項": "", "関連科目": "", "授業の概要・背景": "", "授業方法": "This\ncourse will be offered in a face-to-face format. The class sessions will\nfeature a mix of lectures, discussions, and small-group activities. Class\nreadings will be posted on LUNA.", "トピック": {"第1回": ["<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" times=\"times\" new=\"new\" roman\",serif;\"=\"roman',serif;'\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt;font-family:;\">Introduction\nto the Syllabus</span><span ｍｓ=\"ｍｓ\" 明朝\",serif;mso-ascii-font-family:\"times=\"明朝',serif;mso-ascii-font-family:'times\" new=\"new\" roman\";mso-fareast-theme-font:minor-fareast;mso-hansi-font-family:\"times=\"roman';mso-fareast-theme-font:minor-fareast;mso-hansi-font-family:'times\" roman\";mso-bidi-font-family:\"times=\"roman';mso-bidi-font-family:'times\" roman\";\"=\"roman';'\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt;font-fa